HEADWORD: Poly-mountain
<hw>Po`ly-moun"tain</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Same as <er>Poly</er>, <pos>n.</pos></def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The closely related <spn>Teucrium montanum</spn>,
formerly called <spn>Polium montanum</spn>, a plant of Southern
Europe.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The <spn>Bartsia alpina</spn>, a low
purple-flowered herb of Europe.</def>⟦br⟧
